			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>Evaluating the Usability of a Visual Feature Modeling Notation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AleksandarJakšic.html">Aleksandar Jakšic</a>, <a href="../profile/RobertBFrance.html">Robert B. France</a>, <a href="../profile/PhilippeCollet.html">Philippe Collet</a>, <a href="../profile/SudiptoGhosh.html">Sudipto Ghosh</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_7">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_7</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagM">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s main contribution is a usability-focused enhancement and assessment of feature-model notations.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagL">T4F: Visualisation</span></a><ul><li> It introduces/uses visualization (feature diagram rendering) to improve understanding of feature models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2c.html"><span class="tagL">T2C: Variability</span></a><ul><li> Feature modeling is a central technique for product lines and variability management.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It reports an evaluation study to assess the impact of the proposed notation/tool support.
</li></ul></li></ul>
